{
  "texts": [
    "Open-source LLMs used for fine-tuning.",
    "We utilize the instruction fine-tuning 37 method to refine LLMs.",
    "This method primarily involves targeted finetuning based on specific instructions atop the foundational language model, thereby enhancing the LLM's capability to comprehend and respond to user commands or inquiries.",
    "We fine-tuning the model using Instruction-Response pairs, where the Instructions serve as input data and the Responses are treated as labels.",
    "During the fine-tuning phase, the optimization algorithm modifies the LLM's parameters by calculating the loss function between the predicted outputs and the actual labels."
  ]
}